03/12/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police arrested a suspect Tuesday (December 2nd) in connection with Monday's bombing at an office of the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) in Istanbul. 
The detainee worked in a natural gas company. 
A little known terrorist organisation calling itself "Revolutionist Headquarters" claims responsibility for the attack. 
(Sabah, Zaman - 03/12/08)
